The paper discusses a novel method for deep reinforcement learning with parameterised action spaces, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on Q-networks, which are a type of deep learning model commonly used in reinforcement learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with robotics (Robot Soccer Goal), control (Half Field Offense), and computer vision (Platform), which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also likely sub-categories.
